---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { site } from "../site.config";

const updated = "June 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={`How ${site.name} handles your data: your video is compressed on your device and never uploaded.`}
  path="/privacy/"
>
  <Header />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-[760px] px-6 md:px-12 py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.06em] text-[var(--color-fg-subtle)]">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--color-fg-subtle)]">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-[var(--color-fg-muted)] leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        The short version: <strong class="text-[var(--color-fg)]">your video is
        compressed entirely on your own device and is never uploaded to us or
        anyone else.</strong> {site.name} has no server that receives your files.
      </p>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">How compression works</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          {site.name} compresses video using WebAssembly that runs inside your browser.
          When you choose a video, it's read into your browser's memory and processed
          locally — it never travels across the internet. The only thing downloaded from
          the network is the compressor program itself (a WebAssembly module), which is
          code, not your data.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">What we collect</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          No accounts, no logins, no uploaded files. We do not receive, store, or have
          any access to the videos you compress.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Analytics</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We may use privacy-respecting, aggregate analytics to count page views and
          understand which features are used. It never has access to your videos and does
          not identify you. If enabled, it loads only on the production site.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Hosting</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The site is served as static files by a content-delivery network, which may
          process standard non-identifying request logs (such as IP address and user
          agent) for security and reliability. This is never combined with your video
          content, which the CDN never sees.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Children's privacy</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          {site.name} is a general-audience utility and collects no personal data from
          anyone, including children under 13.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Changes & contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          If this policy changes, the “last updated” date will change with it. Questions?
          Email
          <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`} class="text-[var(--color-accent)] underline">{site.contactEmail}</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
